<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>

<head>
    <title>Image Compressor</title>
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href="/img/logo.png" type="image/x-icon">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
    <script type="text/javascript"
        src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/browser-image-compression@1.0.17/dist/browser-image-compression.js"></script>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
</head>

<body>
    {{>header}}
    <div class="container">
        <div class="main-content">
            <form>
                <div class="control">
                    {{!-- <input type="file" id="upload"> --}}
                    <div class="file-input">
                        <input type="file" id="upload" class="file">
                        <label for="upload">
                            Select file
                        </label>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="control" style="padding: 0 0 0 10px;">
                    <p class="file-name"></p>
                </div>
                <div class="control">
                    <span style="margin-right: 65px;">MaxSizeMB:</span><input id="fileSize" type="number" value="1">
                </div>
                <div class="control">
                    <span style="margin-right: 15px;">MaxWidthOrHeight:</span> <input type="number" id="maxWidthOrHeight"
                        value="1024">
                </div>
                <div class="control" id="controlBtns">
                    <button>Preview</button>
                </div>

            </form>
        </div>
        <div class="image-container">
            <div class="input-output-container input-preview">
                <span class="size" id="input-size"></span>
                <img id="input-image" />
            </div>
            <div class="input-output-container output-preview">
                <span class="size" id="output-size"></span>
                <img id="output-image" />
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="image-compression-details">
            <h3 class="detail-title">What is image compression?</h3>
            <aside>Image compression is an application of data compression that encodes the original image with few
                bits.
                The objective of image compression is to reduce the redundancy of the image and to store or transmit
                data in
                an efficient form.</aside>
            <p>At its core, image compression is when you remove or group together certain parts of an image file in
                order
                to reduce its size. Why do that? Here are a few reasons.</p>
            <ul>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">For website optimization. Sites with uncompressed images can take
                    longer to
                    load, and can cause your
                    visitors to bounce because of this.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">For reducing the storage impact on your hard drive.
                </li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;">For sending and uploading images. Uploading an uncompressed image can
                    take
                    a while, and some email
                    servers have a file size limit.</li>
            </ul>

        </div>
    </div>
    {{>footer}}
    <script src="/js/compressor.js"></script>
</body>

</html>